author: ETA PRIME
description:
Lenovo’s new Legion Pro 5 Gen 10 is here—and the 16” 165Hz OLED might be the best part. I’ve had it for a few days and in this first look we’ll go over the design, ports, Legion Space performance modes, benchmarks, and real gaming tests at 1600p / 1440p.
This config: Ryzen 7 8745H, RTX 5060 Laptop (8GB), 32GB DDR5, 2560x1600 OLED 165Hz (HDR1000), Wi-Fi 7, 80Wh battery.
If there’s anything you want to see tested on the Legion Pro 5 Gen 10, drop it in the comments!
